ds_post$count
ds_post$results |&gt; purse()


Simple GET equivalent of a POST query. Note that parameters containing arrays or objects are not yet supported by SwaggerUI. For conditions, sorts, and other complex parameters, write your query in JSON and then convert to a nested query string. See this web tool for an example.


request("https://data.cms.gov/provider-data/api/1/datastore/query/f93da3a3-400b-5efe-960d-c1d72b1d4f65") |&gt;
  req_url_query(
    limit                     = 1,
    offset                    = 10,
    count                     = "true",
    results                   = "true",
    schema                    = "true",
    keys                      = "true",
    format                    = "json",
    rowIds                    = "false",
    `conditions[0][property]` = "record_number",
    `conditions[0][value]`    = 1,
    `conditions[0][operator]` = "&gt;") |&gt; 
  req_perform() |&gt; 
  resp_body_string() |&gt; 
  jsonify::pretty_json()



